Unhandled errors in route handlers will leak stack traces to the client (Express's default behavior in development), exposing internal implementation details.

**5. No input validation/sanitization on `/users`**
While currently just returning static data, there's no pattern in place for validating query parameters (e.g., `?id=`, `?name=`). If this route evolves to accept filters, it'll be vulnerable to injection.

